Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Pour @cold salted water{300%ml} (double for 4p) into a medium #pot{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @jasmine rice{150%g} and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower the heat to medium, cover with the lid and cook for ~{12%minutes}.

Remove the pot from the heat and keep covered for another ~{12%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).



Trim the @carrot{1}(trimmed) (no need to peel), quarter lengthways and chop widthways into small pieces.

Halve, deseed and roughly chop the @bell pepper{1}(halved, deseeded and roughly chopped).

Peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced) into rings.

Zest half the @lime{1/2}(zested). Cut into quarters.

Stir the @coconut milk{1%pack} (or shake the packet) to dissolve any lumps.



Pat the @salmon{200%g} dry with #kitchen paper{}. IMPORTANT: Wash hands after handling raw fish.

Pop onto a lined #baking tray{}, skin-side down.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste} and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Roast on the middle shelf until cooked through, ~{10-15%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Fish is cooked when opaque in the middle.



Meanwhile, place a #pan{} over medium-high heat with enough @oil{to taste} to completely cover the bottom.

Once hot, add the onion rings and cook, stirring carefully, until golden brown, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once cooked, transfer to a #plate{} lined with kitchen paper and season with @salt{to taste}. Set aside to crisp up.

Discard excess oil from the pan so only a drizzle remains.



Return the pan to medium-high heat.

Add the carrots and pepper and cook until softened, ~{5-6%minutes}, then add the @red Thai style paste{1%sachet} and cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add the coconut milk, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water{100%ml} (double both for 4p).

Season with salt and pepper. Stir together and cook until the veg is tender, a further ~{2%minutes}.

Squeeze in the juice of one lime wedge (double for 4p), taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.



Stir the lime zest through the rice, fluffing it up as you go.

Pop the rice into one side of a #bowl{}, spoon the curry next to it, then top with the salmon.

Scatter the crispy onion rings over the top.

Serve remaining lime wedges alongside for squeezing over.